## TLS / Caddy

`*.welpes.com` resolves — LAN-only, via Pi-hole above — to Caddy
({{ hostvars['caddy'].ansible_host }}), which terminates TLS with real Let's
Encrypt certificates (DNS-01 challenge against Cloudflare, scoped to the
`welpes.com` zone) and reverse-proxies each request to the matching service.
Nothing is exposed to the internet: no port forwarding, no public DNS
records.

